Python API Development Course

Welcome to the Python API Development Course repository! This course is designed to provide you with comprehensive knowledge and practical skills in building APIs using Python with FastAPI. Throughout this course, you'll learn fundamental concepts of API design, database integration, testing, and deployment.

Course Overview

In this course, you'll cover the following topics:

Setting up development environment on both Mac and Windows
Python virtual environment basics
Starting with FastAPI and understanding path operations
HTTP requests and schema validation with Pydantic
CRUD operations and storing data
Introduction to databases and SQL
Database CRUD operations using SQLAlchemy
Implementing authentication and authorization with JWT tokens
Advanced topics such as SQL relationships, joins, and migrations
Deploying the API to Heroku and Ubuntu server
Dockerizing the application for containerized deployment
Writing tests using pytest and setting up CI/CD pipeline with GitHub Actions
Course Content

The course is structured into the following sections:

Introduction and project overview
Setting up development environment
Building APIs with FastAPI
Database integration and SQL fundamentals
Authentication and authorization
Advanced topics including SQL relationships and joins
Deployment on Heroku and Ubuntu server
Dockerizing the application
Writing tests and setting up CI/CD pipeline
Prerequisites

Before starting the course, ensure you have the following prerequisites:

Basic knowledge of Python programming language
Familiarity with command line interface
Access to a text editor such as Visual Studio Code
Git and GitHub account for version control
