Course Tools

Python Virtual Environment Management
Creation and management of Python virtual environments for project isolation.
PostgreSQL GUI Management
PgAdmin (for managing PostgreSQL databases through a graphical user interface).
API Testing
Postman collections for testing API endpoints and saving requests.
Database Migrations
Alembic for managing database schema changes and migrations.
Text Editor
Visual Studio Code (VS Code) for writing and editing code.
Course Workflow

The course covers setting up a development environment, creating APIs with FastAPI, integrating with databases using SQLAlchemy, writing tests with Pytest, deploying applications to Heroku and Ubuntu Server, containerizing applications with Docker, and setting up CI/CD pipelines with GitHub Actions.

This technology stack and workflow provide a comprehensive foundation for learning Python API development and related technologies.

Getting Started

To get started with the course, follow these steps:

Clone the repository to your local machine:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/Sanjeev-Thiyagaraj...
Navigate to the repository directory:
bash
Copy code
cd Python-API-Development-Course
Follow the course videos sequentially and complete the exercises provided.
If you encounter any issues or have questions, feel free to reach out to the course instructor or community for assistance.
